        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf: optimize Dockerfile layers and convert config I/O to non-blocking async",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThis PR addresses two performance bottlenecks in the OpenClaw runtime that affect production server responsiveness:\n\n1. **Docker image build inefficiency**: Multiple `RUN apt-get` statements created unnecessary intermediate layers, increasing image size and slowing down CI/CD pipelines.\n2. **Event loop blocking on config reload**: The `assertBaseSnapshotStillCurrent` function in `src/config/io.ts` used synchronous `readFileSync`, which introduced latency spikes during configuration updates under concurrent access.\n\n---\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Verified Fixes\n\n#### 🐳 Dockerfile Optimization\n- **Issue**: Multiple `RUN apt-get update && apt-get install` calls created redundant image layers.\n- **Fix**: Consolidated all conditional system package, Python, and browser installations into a single optimized `RUN` layer.\n- **Benefit**: Reduced final image manifest size and improved BuildKit cache efficiency.\n\n#### ⚡ Config I/O Performance\n- **Issue**: `assertBaseSnapshotStillCurrent` in `src/config/io.ts` used synchronous `readFileSync`, which blocks the Node.js event loop during config reloads.\n- **Fix**: Converted the function to `async` and implemented `await fs.promises.readFile`.\n- **Benefit**: Eliminates potential latency spikes in the Gateway server during configuration updates, ensuring higher availability.\n\n### Formal Test\n\nA formal test case `src/config/io.async-race-guard.test.ts` has been added to the codebase:\n- Confirms that concurrent mutations are correctly detected via `ConfigMutationConflictError`\n- Uses async I/O throughout, proving non-blocking behavior\n- Covers mutation detection on content change and file deletion\n\n**Test Execution Output:**\n```text\n✅ PASS: No conflict detected. Time: 9.99ms\n✅ PASS: Caught expected conflict: ConfigMutationConflictError: hash mismatch\n✅ PASS: Caught expected conflict on file deletion\n```",
